# Security

## Always

- Treat user input, API responses, environment variables, URLs, file paths, and external data as untrusted.
- Validate and normalize data at system boundaries.
- Avoid exposing secrets in source code, logs, errors, test fixtures, URLs, or client bundles.
- Never hardcode credentials, tokens, private keys, or production secrets.
- Prefer safe platform APIs over manual escaping or ad hoc sanitization.
- Avoid unsafe HTML rendering, dynamic code execution, and shell command construction from untrusted input.
- Use least privilege for permissions, tokens, file access, and network access.
- Fail closed for authorization, authentication, and permission checks.